<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>1) Make sure the models for both Horses and Elementals *and* your Race/Gender combination are on, and <br /> <br />2) Open the file in your EQ directory called <span style="color: navy;">eqclient.ini</span> and look for a line that says: <br /> <br />AllLuclinPcModelsOff=FALSE <br /> <br />If it is set to TRUE, then changing it to FALSE will fix your problem. <br /> <br />[EDIT: If that still doesn't work, then you will probably have to buy the <a href="HTTP://everquest.station.sony.com/luclin.jsp" rel="external nofollow" title="everquest.station.sony.com/luclin.jsp">Shadows of Luclin</a> expansion to use it.] <br /> <br /><em class="fs8">Edited, Mon Nov 15 03:46:59 2004</em></p>
