<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>There is no reason to do this quest. <br />If you talk with Sir Ariam Arcanum, he gives you the ghostly bridle.  That will summon a horse.  There is no need to waste your time doing the rest of the quest just to have the same item you are holding renamed to Bridle of Sir Arium.  Go outside and right click your ghostly bridle, whamo a horse shows up.  If you thought that you would have a free horse permanently from this, I am sorry you wasted your time. The day SOE would give anyone that wanted it a free horse, is the day my druid can start ressurecting people.  But it is a nice way to experience a horse without having to purchase one, even if it is only a temporary thing.</p>
